Description:

H. iberomaroccana

morphotype 1 having light brown body (
Fig. 6A
) with narrow frontoclypeal apotome and straight anterior edge and with light (
Fig. 6A
) or dark (
Fig. 6B
) oral spot and blurred V-shaped aboral spot (
Fig. 6B
). 

Hydropsyche iberomaroccana

morphotype 2 (
Fig. 7A
) body having brown color slightly darker than morphotype 1, with dark oral spot as well as barely visible round aboral spot (
Fig. 7B
; 
Table 2
). Both morphotypes having submentum with long lateral lobes (
Figs 6C
, 
7C
) and posterior prosternites pigmented (
Figs 6D
, 
7D
).

It is a rheophilic, alpine, and high mountain species which is also recorded in hills and plains, it has a wide altitudinal distribution from 3100 m a.s.l. to below 200 m a.s.l. (
Graf et al. 2008
). It is an epirhithral and metarhitrhal species showing a preference for coarse gravel, stones, boulders, and bedrock substrates (
Graf et al . 2008
).
